    <name>
				<text>10.2.3.10 Polar form</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<p>If \( \displaystyle{z_1 = {@z1@}} \) and \(\displaystyle{ z_2 = {@z2@} }\), evaluate in polar form:&nbsp;</p>

<li><p>\(\displaystyle{z_1 z_2 = }\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p> \( \dfrac{z_1}{z_2} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>

<li><p>\( \dfrac{z_2}{z_1} = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt3]]<br></p></li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
<p>Our complex numbers are \( z_1 = {@z1@}\) and \( z_2 = {@z2@}\).</p>
  <li>
<p>\( z_1 z_2 = {@ta1@} \)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
<p> \( \dfrac{z_1}{z_2} = {@ta2@}\)&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p> \( \dfrac{z_2}{z_1} = {@ta3@} \)</p>
  </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
